{"_id":"CidScEy5HMRrYaXG","name":"Dark Ego - Alice of Other Worlds","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>Alice of\nOther Worlds\nAs a child I traveled to other worlds and my mind can perceive and see \nthings beyond common perception. Memories of my childhood haunt me, \nand I often get lost in visions of the past.<h3>Dark Ego</h3>As an action, you may spend \n1 Soma to try to possess the body of a person or animal that is looking into \nyour eyes. Particularly powerful individuals may require a Position Check for \nyou to succeed. Y ou can act through the body you possess and continue to use \nyour Gifts and Descriptors, but you receive an additional Descriptor created \nby the Storyteller and representing the abilities of the body you are possessing. \nThe possession ends at the end of the Scene, when the possessed body suffers 1 \nWound, or you decide to return to your body of your own volition. While you \ncontrol someone else’s body, your original body is inert and at the mercy of the \nworld. Y ou cannot possess Broken Tales or supernatural creatures. Y our mind is \nnot easy to control, so you gain 1 Additional Success for Defense Checks against \nany kind of mind control and magic.","notes":"Alice of Other Worlds - bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 2.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"You notice a detail that does not match what you consider normal.\nXP\nSoma\n 5"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241693,"modifiedTime":1783973241693,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"CWDhSgU35OFKvtxf","name":"Dark Ego - Beasts in Body and Soul","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am linked to Dionysus and we share pain and perceptions. He will \nalways know where I am and vice versa. For me, that’s the most \nhumiliating part of the curse.<h3>Dark Ego</h3>When you reveal your \ntrue nature everyone is horrified. One is a beast in body, while the other \nis a beast in her soul. Y ou receive 3 Savagery Tokens that you can spend \nduring the Scene to: \n1. Inflict 1 additional Wound, if Dionysus spends an action to help you in \nthe attack. The Wound will be a strikingly bloody gash.\n2. Have a minor NPC lose their action as they are intimidated, having \nwitnessed the fury of Dionysus.\n3. If Dionysus is not present in the Scene, he can appear immediately \n(possibly tearing a new opening in the environment, demolishing any \npossible obstacle) to support you. \n4. Perform a second action in the Exchange, if Dionysus spends one of his \nto open the way for you.","notes":"Beauty and her Beast - bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 4.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Unleash the feral power of Dionysus, or humiliate or betray \nsomeone, revealing your true nature."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241693,"modifiedTime":1783973241693,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"FyiPbkfPtesW9tkz","name":"Dark Ego - Pure Innocence","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3><h3>Dark Ego</h3>When you appeal to the \npurity of your heart, even the foulest spell is broken. When you \nactivate your Dark Ego during a Scene, you become immune to \nany effect of fear or mind control, and all subjects you consider evil \nlower their Opposition Level by 1 in your presence. Y ou can spend 1 \nMutation Token to give 1 Additional Success to the first action of all \nallies who admire you for who you are.","notes":"Bloodwhite - bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 6.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Open your heart and appeal to the goodness of those close to \nyou, revealing who you are, or sacrifice something of yourself for others.\nXP\nSoma\n 5"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241693,"modifiedTime":1783973241693,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"RrJuN1n2cLyHMyLP","name":"Dark Ego - Soulless Puppet","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3><h3>Dark Ego</h3>Y our body is made of wood and \nso you ignore any penalty derived from dangers that would affect a living \nbeing. Y ou receive 1 Additional Success to all your Defense Checks. Y ou \ncan communicate with other puppets or toys who can tell you something \nat the Storyteller’s discretion. If you stay still, you will pass as a common \npuppet in the eyes of those who see you and you cannot be discovered \nexcept with special skills or magic.","notes":"Wound. Carlo the LivingPuppet - bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 8.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Make obvious use of the wooden properties of your body to perform \nan action, or have your nose grow dramatically (i.e. when you accumulate \nthe third Lie Token), proving to everyone that you are not human."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241693,"modifiedTime":1783973241693,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"UuF4EVz4vYZqqMR5","name":"Dark Ego - Mad like a Hatter","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3><h3>Dark Ego</h3>When you give free rein to \nyour madness, reality bends itself to prove you right. Declare something \ncrazy such as That door leads to the opposite side of town, or This pair \nof glasses allows you to see ghosts and create a Descriptor. Y our madness \nmust always concern an object and its crazy use. Y ou cannot directly affect \nor interact with living beings. Suffer 1 Wound caused by the fatigue of \nturning your madness into reality. Y our madness lasts throughout the \nScene. If at least one subject is amazed by what you do with your madness, \nyou gain 1 Soma.","notes":"Hatta Carter - bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 10.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Behave and talk like a crazy person, not worrying about the \nreactions of those around you."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241693,"modifiedTime":1783973241693,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"zDMwqZTnhYKSOJ1H","name":"Dark Ego - The Headless Knight","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3><h3>Dark Ego</h3>Y ou are an immortal \nvengeful spirit. When you suffer your last Wound, you dissolve into \nthin air to return at the beginning of the next Scene having recovered 2","notes":"The Knight with a Hundred Heads - bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 12.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":""},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241694,"modifiedTime":1783973241694,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"ThEjMveNoiXwksj9","name":"Dark Ego - The Young Wolf","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>Iskra the\n Young\nWolf I am a wolf child and I defend myself with fangs and claws. My \nsense of smell is infallible. I’m young and I know little about the \nworld, so I am easily intimidated when I face something I don’t \nknow.<h3>Dark Ego</h3>Unleash your feral side, ready to bite anyone who opposes your pack. If you get an Outcome with an \nIncrement on a Position Check, you can spend the Increment to take an \nadditional action immediately. Y ou can also inflict 1 Wound on yourself \nto perform an additional action after your normal action. Y ou can’t \nperform more than 3 actions per Exchange. Y ou may spend 1 Soma \nto memorize the smell of a person you are interacting with. Y ou will \nalways recognize them and it will be easy for you to follow their tracks \neven after a long time.","notes":"Iskra the Young Wolf - bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 14.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Give free rein to your feral side or fulfill a task for your pack with your wolf skills.\nXP\nSoma\n 6"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241694,"modifiedTime":1783973241694,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"e0c6tk9ec0MB6ays","name":"Dark Ego - Our Home","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>We are capable builders and there is no building that we cannot fortify or infiltrate. We \nare very protective of what we think is ours.<h3>Dark Ego</h3>When you arrive in a new location, you can take the \ntime to examine, alter, and repair it. Y ou may use one of the following options for each \npresent gang member.\n1. Escape route: Detail a Descriptor that represents an escape route that only you \nmay open.\n2. Trap: Detail a Descriptor that describes how your trap activates and hurts intruders. \nThose who enter the perimeter will trigger it, suffering 1 Wound. Skilled and attentive \nindividuals may require a Position Check to fall into your trap.\n3. Improvement: Create a Descriptor that represents an improvement you make to \nthe environment. Y ou get 1 Additional Success when you make use of your improvement \nduring an action.\n4. Alter: Detail a Descriptor that represents a new feature of the site that only you can \nactivate.","notes":"The Gang of three Pigs - bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 16.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Take time to work on a location and make it your own."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241694,"modifiedTime":1783973241694,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"em34yFhYBydgLnEJ","name":"Dark Ego - The Supreme Fairy","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3><h3>Dark Ego</h3>Y ou can unleash your true \nfairy essence and alter reality itself. When you do this, you suffer 1 Wound \nand choose an effect:\n1. Making the Unreal a Reality: One of your illusions becomes \nreal. If necessary, the Storyteller must create an ad hoc profile.\n2. Supreme Fairy: Y ou may replicate a Gift with a magical effect you \nhave witnessed at least once during the Scenario, for the duration of the \nScene.\n3. Lady of Destiny: Y ou can change the fate of a Minor NPC by \nrewriting its Descriptor and Agenda. This may not affect particularly \npowerful NPCs or enemies, at the Storyteller’s discretion.","notes":"Morgana of the Lake - bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 18.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Evoke your true potential when experiencing a strong emotion or \nwhen you find yourself in a magically charged location, and let yourself be \nflooded with power."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241694,"modifiedTime":1783973241694,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"BvaYgVaAclN2Ehf9","name":"Dark Ego - From Another World","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am a person out of her time and largely immune to those who use spells and \nmagic. I have a natural talent for fighting those who use magic. I hate witches \nand sorcerers because, despite their power, they can’t heal me.<h3>Dark Ego</h3>As a creature displaced in time, you \nare naturally resistant to magic. Y ou gain 2 Additional Successes when defending \nyourself from a danger associated with magic. When you inflict 1 Wound on a \nbeing associated with magic, you prevent them from using their powers (Gifts and \nDescriptors) during their next action. Blocking the powers of particularly powerful \nopponents and Hunters may require a Position Check. When you touch a magic or \nenchanted object, you can spend 1 Soma to temporarily interrupt its power. The \nduration of this effect is decided by the Storyteller.","notes":"OZena the Suffering - bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 20.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Reveal that you’re from another time through a gesture or a word. \nAlternatively, act threatening towards a magical being."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241694,"modifiedTime":1783973241694,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"iUr6oheUUZcRr9Dq","name":"Dark Ego - One Thousand and One Nights","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>Sherazade \nthe Weaver of \nTales\nMy stories become reality. Shadows, those ubiquitous reflections of \nreality, can interact with me. A life among the shadows in my bedroom \nhas made it hard for me to bear sunlight.<h3>Dark Ego</h3>One of the \ncharacters in a story you told during the Session comes to life as a Shadow. \nCreate a Descriptor for them, ensuring it is driven to support you. The \nShadow could, for example, fly or walk on water. The Shadow thus created \nwill be at your service and will do whatever you order with an OL Medium 5 \nand 1 Wound. For each Story Token you decide to spend, you can summon \nan additional Shadow. Y our Shadows do not speak and cannot act in places \nwhere there is more light than darkness.","notes":"Sherazade the Weaver of Tales - bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 22.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Manifest your affinity for the shadows or tell a dark story full of \nfear and monsters.\nXP\nSoma\n 6"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241694,"modifiedTime":1783973241694,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"SITXQaIu3RUAcHO4","name":"Dark Ego - The Sleeping Will","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I can move objects with the power of thought alone. Through this power, \nI am able to manifest my presence in the world. My real body is immobile \nand locked in eternal sleep, at the mercy of the world. I long for the \nleast caress, which would remind me of being alive.<h3>Dark Ego</h3>Y ou can use your power to \nmanipulate the objects around you. Y ou can make small items float or \nthrow them like weapons. Y ou can affect your surroundings up to 30 feet \naway. Y ou can act up to 3 times in an Exchange, manipulating the world \naround you, but you cannot act more than once against the same target. \nOnce per Scene, you can focus all 3 actions on a single large object (like a \nhouse) and manipulate it to your liking.","notes":"Talia the Sleeper - bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 24.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Shed your cloak, revealing your helpless body or exposing yourself \nto others by manipulating the world around you."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241694,"modifiedTime":1783973241694,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"F72yZCjfpZmurLss","name":"Dark Ego – Solitary Ghost","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3><h3>Dark Ego</h3>When you decide to take on your ghostly \nform, you receive 1 Solitude Token and become intangible. Y ou cannot have any kind \nof physical interaction with the world (not even talking) and no one can touch you, \nexcept through magic. However, you do not become invisible to the human eye and so \nthose who see you will understand that you are a ghost. In the form of a specter, your \naffinity to fire is more intense and you gain 1 Additional Success in any action involving \nthe flames you are manipulating. In addition, you can spend 1 Soma to ignite a flame \nfrom thin air and set something on fire. The effect of this Gift lasts until you decide to \nstop it, but the Storyteller can spend 1 Solitude Token to force you to remain ethereal \nfor a few more minutes. When you take an Interlude or spend time with someone who cares about you, remove all Solitude Tokens. When you use this Gift without satisfying \nthe Activator, you can ignore the Wound and take 1 Solitude Token instead.","notes":"Yvonne of the Dark - bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf, pages 26.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"React angrily when the world ignores you or makes it clear to you that no one cares about you."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241694,"modifiedTime":1783973241694,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
